![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/5ea997c9-f13b-4e10-ae94-5c2abf045558/372.jpg)

Hell’s Kitchen just got a little darker. This week on the _Major Issues Podcast_, we’re diving deep into the first nine issues of Charles Soule’s _Daredevil_ run, where Matt Murdock is back in black, back in New York, and—somehow—his identity is a secret again?! With a mysterious new sidekick, a dangerous new foe, and a whole new status quo, Soule takes the Man Without Fear into uncharted territory. How did Daredevil pull off the impossible? What makes this run stand out from what came before? And does Matt ever catch a break? Join us as we unravel the secrets, the action, and the legal drama that makes _Daredevil_ one of Marvel’s most compelling heroes. Tune in—justice is blind, but you don’t have to be!

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

